This paper deals with analyzing Twitter data, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the biases introduced by data acquisition techniques, which involves statistical inference and machine learning, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also analyzes the effects of demographics on language use, which falls under the category of social computing, making cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper uses a latent variable model, which involves statistical modeling and inference, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category as well.
